td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Discovery of a Dusty Place</span><hr size=1> It poked him from the back of his mind, even after Ninou and he had disappeared from the West Commonlands in a burst of Druidic teleportation magic to appear in the Karanas.<br>
Had that been a light in the window of the old building near Kithicor?<br>
The next day, his short legs pumping with the Spirit of the Wolf, he passed through deadly Kithicor back into the Commonlands.  Surely he had been mistaken, a play of moonlight upon darkened glass.<br>
<br>
But there it stood, The Missed Note.  A thin line of smoke rising from the chimney and the faint sounds of singing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Xanta?&quot;  Dorraxx poked his head in the door as memories flashed through his head.  Had it been that long?<br>
<br>
The High Elven Cleric was moving about the main room, wiping away some of the dust and cobwebs that had gathered over the months.  He watched her, mesmerized momentarily at her grace as she stepped lightly from the tables to the bar and back.  She carried a glass of wine in one hand and was singing a lilting tune he didn't recognize.  It was no wonder she had won Darkmask's heart.<br>
&quot;Xanta?&quot;  <br>
She turned toward the doorway and smiled.  &quot;Dorraxx!&quot;  She motioned him to the various spirits she had gathered from behind the bar. &quot;Join me for a drink?&quot;<br>
He tilted his head and grinned, &quot;Don't mind if I do.&quot;  He approached and, choosing the brandy, poured a glass.<br>
Peering at Xanta, a bemused grin on his face, he asked, &quot;So, what brings ye here?&quot; <p><center><hr size=5, width="55%">

