<br>
How many still remained he was unsure.  But just as a strong need for isolation drove him away so long ago, I new need for company and the presence of friends now brought him back.<br>
<br>
Walking over the crest of a hill he spotted the Missed Note.  So much like he had first seen it years ago.  He saw smoke trailing from the chimney and hope arose with in.  Would any of his friends still be there, Sasi, Lodach, Myethia, Dorraxx or Kalaz and so many others.  Or would he be walking in on a bunch of strangers who have no memory of him?  Well their was only one way to find out he thought as he made his way down the slope to the cozy inn below.   <p><center><font face="lucida handwriting, arial" color="006800" size=+2><b>Radgen Warenherz</font></b><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="675f00" size=+1><b>Pathfinder of Karana</font><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="blue" size=+1>Shining Path</font></b><br><img src=http://radgen.homestead.com/files/tiger_run_md_clr.gif></center>
