<br>
His fingers stroked over the gold crest on top of the compass lid, and he flipped it open, he knew this compass though was magical, and didnt tell the owner where north was, but where Xanta was.<br>
<br>
Darkmask was susprised at the magic Xanta had, for a cleric, she always seemed to glow with much more power then healer, and sometimes she would often show him fantastic trinkets. In fact, Darkmask was battering for class v gnomish batteries for Xanta now.<br>
<br>
He watched as Ping Fuzzlecutter showed him his supply and talked and talked like most gnomes do, explaining how the mana in the air was compressed into these small boxes and could be discharged through contact with certain metals..Darkmask didnt really understand what tinkerers did, but he loved their toys.<br>
<br>
Gathering a few more tinkered items from Ping, he worked out a price, and paid the little man. Flipping the compass open, it glowed with blue power, and pointed Darkmask to the commonlands.<br>
<br>
Not wanting to create commotion and attract the guards of freeport, Darkmask surrounded himself in a cloak of invisibility, his magic was ackward now, it didnt flow like it used before his...death in Droga, it was almost like he didnt have the magic in him, but was now borrowing it from someone, he worried if the person he pulled on felt his tug every spell he cast.<br>
<br>
Entering the open hills of the commons, Darkmask headed towards the druid ring, figuring his love might be there, healing, and tending to wounds, but she wasnt in sight. He flipped open his compass and she appeared to be further on, this was not unexpected as she often wandered and followed the occasional animal, she was so curious and sometimes got lost in nature itself, she was truely a child of Tunare.<br>
<br>
As his eyes were watching the compass, he came over a hill, to see a sight he hadnt seen in years...The Missed Note....it was lit up...<br>
<br>
Quickly he dropped his spell,and hastened his pace, thinking of seeing his friends again, he heard tales of them, but to see them again, how glorious would that be....<br>
<br>
Darkmask smiled to himself, thinking of Harte, Sasi, Pikel, Thistleburr, Vandaal, Gulasx, the Myth, Dorraxx, Radgen, Len, even Ninou...so many faces he had long missed, so many lives he felt he lost contact with.....<br>
<br>
He heard singing as he came to the window, he knew it to be his love, her voice is unlike that of any other woman, sweet, stirring and magical, Darkmask stopped to see her, to watch her, she was amazing....a smile crossed his face.....<br>
<br>
He heard a voice he hadnt heard in quite awhile inside, the gruff voice of Dorraxx, he knew it well, as Dorraxx was considered something of a wise advisor whom was sought out for his council and fair judgement, Darkmask remembered well the nights he stayed up discussing matters with him, and how when everyone though Darkmask took advantage of Ninou, he was there to temper their anger and see the situation for what it was....<br>
<br>
....he slid the compass into his pocket and entered the Missed Note.... <p><center>
