<br>
Laughter spilled out through the window, beckoning her.. How can I go right in, I am lost to these people..? Sighing, she pulled her cloak tightly about her and turned to continue past, as she always did..her staff drooping slightly.<br>
<br>
A thought struck her..so long ago it seemed, that she had silently stood in the shadows, straining to overhear the glorious stories of her lost dragon.. hoping against hope that he would return to her. Mayhaps, she thought, I could go in.. just for a moment.. <br>
<br>
She spied Xanta through the window, the love radiating from her as always, filling the room with a soft glow. ..I would like to go in.. She pushed through the doorway and found a seat off from the others and the bar, her head turned downward. After all this time.. she had come through the door.<br>
<br>
