<br>
She remembered her short stint as a waitress there and her first meeting with Radgen, Dorraxx, Myethia, Harte, Sasi, Darkmask and others.  Her first night there had been a harsh one....She had healed a chanter who had been Harm Touched by a sleeping SK who had screamed while having a nightmare.  She had been so young back then...and had since learned so much.<br>
<br>
She strolled through the commons towards Kithicor knowing she had to make it through the woods before nightfall or camp on this side for a night.  But oh how she wanted a good wine this night and a soft bed.  <br>
<br>
She looked ahead of her and a small wisp of smoke arose on the horizon wear the Missed Note once stood...<br>
<br>
"It can't be possible.  Can it?" Lodach thought to herself as her feet changed direction and followed the smoke.  She entered the old cleared and sure enough there was the Note with signs of life coming from its doors.  She couldn't believe it and stood silently looking at it from the distance.<br>
<br>
Finally as the shock left her she found herself approuching the door and pushing it open as she once had, so long ago.  With an impish greeting she pushed open the door, "Hello, who did this?  Who awoken the spirit of the Note once more?"<br>
<br>
She looked around and saw some familiar faces and smiled happily.<br>
<br>
"Omg darlings....any chance there is a room availalbe for a few nights for a retired waitress of this place?"<br>
